{
  "texts": [
    "Likewise, the proportion of \"Not Sure\" votes was also computed.",
    "The Thurstone Case V model was then used to compute scale values via maximum-likelihood estimation using the same procedure as in a previous study [53].",
    "For this purpose, a value of 1 was added to the score of a stimulus each time that it was preferred over its pair.",
    "In the case of \"Not Sure\" answers, a value of 0.5 was added to the score of both stimuli.",
    "To avoid the zero-frequency problem for stimuli that were never selected, all scores were initialized to a value of 0.1, corresponding to a \"Not Sure\" answer weighted by 0.2."
  ]
}